🧭 Project Overview

In this project, we use Terraform to create an Amazon Machine Image (AMI) from an existing EC2 instance. An AMI is a reusable template that contains an operating system, installed software, and configurations.

This concept is fundamental in DevOps because it enables immutable infrastructure, where servers are not manually configured but instead launched from pre-built images.

🎯 Objective
Create an AMI from an existing EC2 instance using Terraform
Understand image-based infrastructure provisioning
Learn the concept of immutable infrastructure
Enable repeatable and scalable server deployments

