📌 Concept Explanation

An Amazon Machine Image (AMI) is a snapshot of a running EC2 instance that includes:

Operating system
Installed packages
Application code (if any)
Configuration settings

Once created, an AMI can be used to launch identical EC2 instances.

Why AMIs Matter in DevOps

Without AMIs:

Every server must be configured manually
Deployments are inconsistent
Scaling is slow and error-prone

With AMIs:

Servers are pre-configured
Deployment is fast and consistent
Infrastructure becomes repeatable and versioned
