Implementation
Step 1: Configure AWS Provider
provider "aws" {
  region = "us-east-1"
}
Step 2: Reference Existing EC2 Instance
data "aws_instance" "source" {
  instance_id = "i-0123456789abcdef0"
}
Step 3: Create AMI from EC2 Instance
resource "aws_ami_from_instance" "devops_ami" {
  name               = "devops-custom-ami"
  source_instance_id = data.aws_instance.source.id

  tags = {
    Name = "devops-ami"
  }
}
Explanation
data "aws_instance"
data "aws_instance" "source"

This retrieves information about an existing EC2 instance that will be used as the source for the AMI.

aws_ami_from_instance
resource "aws_ami_from_instance" "devops_ami"

This creates a machine image from the selected EC2 instance.

source_instance_id
source_instance_id = data.aws_instance.source.id

Specifies which EC2 instance will be used as the base for the AMI.

name
name = "devops-custom-ami"

Defines a name for the AMI so it can be identified in AWS.

