🔐 Security Best Practices
Ensure the source instance is hardened before creating AMIs.
Remove sensitive data before image creation.
Avoid embedding credentials inside AMIs.
Tag AMIs for version tracking.
Regularly clean up unused AMIs to reduce storage costs.
💰 Cost Awareness

AMIs are stored in Amazon S3-backed snapshots, and you are billed for:

Snapshot storage
AMI versions retained over time

Always delete outdated AMIs and snapshots to control costs.

