💡 Senior DevOps Insight

At scale, no serious DevOps team manually configures servers.

Instead, they rely on:

Golden Images (AMIs)
Immutable Infrastructure
Automated Deployment Pipelines

The real power of AMIs is not just creating images — it is enabling:

“Every server is identical, reproducible, and disposable.”

This eliminates configuration drift, reduces deployment errors, and allows infrastructure to be rebuilt in minutes rather than hours or days.

Once you understand AMIs, you start thinking less about servers and more about versioned infrastructure artifacts.
